Identify the previous filing by registration statement number, or the Form or Schedule and the date of its filing.</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU2"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">On August 21, 2020, Tesla, Inc. issued the following press release and published the below pages on its website at </font><font style="text-decoration:underline;">www.tesla.com/2020shareholdermeetin</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;">g</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> and </font><font style="text-decoration:underline;">www.tesla.com/2020-meeting-terms</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">:</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt; clear:both;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU3"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">TESLA ANNOUNCES UPDATES TO 2020 ANNUAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS AND BATTERY DAY EVENT</font></p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">PALO ALTO, Calif., August 21, 2020 &#8211; Tesla, Inc. today announced updates to the time, format and location of its 2020 Annual Meeting of Stockholders (the &#8220;<font style="text-decoration:underline;">2020 Annual Meeting</font>&#8221;). Tesla also announced information regarding its separate Battery Day event.</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Although Tesla believes that the best stockholder experience is a fully in-person annual meeting open to all stockholders, continuing public health and travel-related requirements and advisories have necessitated a unique format for the 2020 Annual Meeting. The following updates supersede anything to the contrary described in Tesla&#8217;s updated definitive proxy statement filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on August 13, 2020. </p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Date and Time of Events</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The 2020 Annual Meeting will be held on Tuesday, September 22, 2020, at 1:30 p.m. Pacific Time. </p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s separate Battery Day event will follow immediately after the conclusion of the 2020 Annual Meeting.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Virtual Meeting and Live Video Webcasts</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk48679145"></a>Live video webcasts of the 2020 Annual Meeting and Tesla&#8217;s Battery Day event will be accessible to the general public at <font style="text-decoration:underline;color:#000000;">www.tesla.com/2020shareholdermeeting</font><a name="_Hlk48679145"></a>. </p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To accommodate ongoing public health requirements and travel considerations, Tesla is also providing any stockholder as of July 31, 2020 the means to join the 2020 Annual Meeting virtually at <font style="text-decoration:underline;">www.meetingcenter.io/234436330</font>. The virtual meeting will feature the same live video webcasts accessible to the general public, plus the option to submit votes and written comments on meeting agenda items. In order to join the virtual meeting, you will need the password, which is <font style="font-weight:bold;">tsla2020</font>, and a 15-digit secure &#8220;control number&#8221; unique to you, which you may obtain as follows:</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.85%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.85%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri;">If you are a &#8220;stockholder of record&#8221; with shares registered </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:Calibri;">directly in your name with our transfer agent, Computershare Trust Company</font><font style="font-family:Calibri;"> (a minority of Tesla stockholders), you can find the control number on the Notice of Internet Availability or paper proxy card that was sent to you (</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-family:Calibri;">please check that it is for the meeting as scheduled for September 22, 2020, NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 2020)</font><font style="font-family:Calibri;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.85%;text-indent:-3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.85%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.85%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri;">If you are a &#8220;beneficial owner&#8221; and hold shares through a broker, bank or other organization (the vast majority of Tesla stockholders), you will have to register in advance to obtain a control number. Please ask your broker, bank or organization for a &#8220;legal proxy&#8221; for the 2020 Annual Meeting and submit a copy of it from your e-mail address with &#8220;Legal Proxy&#8221; in the subject line to </font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-family:Calibri;">legalproxy@computershare.com</font><font style="font-family:Calibri;">. If your request is received no later than 2:00 p.m. Pacific Time on September 17, 2020, you will receive a confirmation e-mail with your control number.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Limited In-Person Events</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk48679326"></a><a name="_Hlk48679326"></a>In addition, Tesla expects to accommodate a very limited number of stockholders in-person at the 2020 Annual Meeting and the Battery Day event due to mandated restrictions on the size of in-person gatherings. Both events will be held at:</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla, Inc.<br />901 Page Ave.<br />Fremont, CA 94538</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk48900662"></a><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU4"></a><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We are excited to be able to host attendees in strict accordance </font><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">with a format that provides robust health control measures</font><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">. We will also employ additional safety measures and screening </font><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">protocols to protect our attendees and personnel</font><font style="color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</font></p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To maximize fairness, Tesla will conduct a random drawing to determine stockholders&#8217; eligibility to attend both events in person. If you were a stockholder on July 31, 2020, you may apply for this drawing at <font style="text-decoration:underline;color:#000000;">www.tesla.com/2020shareholdermeeting</font>. The drawing will be held strictly in accordance with the rules and terms described at such website, and we will be unable to make any exceptions. </p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Please note that due to mandated restrictions on the size of in-person gatherings, the total number of people that Tesla may have onsite at the events is very limited. Tesla will not be able to admit anyone to the events except stockholders who have been selected through the drawing and certain Tesla personnel and their guests.</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">However, Tesla will continue to monitor public health and travel safety protocols required or recommended by federal, state and local governments. Tesla may be required to or choose to further change the date, time, location and/or format of the 2020 Annual Meeting, in which case Tesla will publicly announce any further changes in advance.</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Other Information</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.85%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">All stockholders are encouraged to vote and submit their proxies in advance of the 2020 Annual Meeting by one of the methods described in the proxy materials. Proxy cards, voting instruction forms and Notices of Internet Availability for the 2020 Annual Meeting scheduled for September 22, 2020 that were previously distributed will not be updated to reflect the change in meeting time, location or format, and may continue to be used to vote shares in connection with the 2020 Annual Meeting. </p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Investor Relations Contact:</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">ir@tesla.com</font></p>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU7"></a><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Livestream&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Virtual Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To accommodate ongoing public health requirements and travel considerations, we are also&nbsp;&nbsp;providing any stockholder as of July 31, 2020 the means to join the 2020 Annual Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;virtually at www.meetingcenter.io/234436330.</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> The virtual meeting will feature the same live&nbsp;&nbsp;video webcasts accessible to the general public above, plus the option to submit votes and&nbsp;&nbsp;written comments on meeting agenda items. In order to join the virtual meeting, you will&nbsp;&nbsp;need the password, which </font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">is tsla2020, and a 15-digit secure &#8220;control number&#8221; unique to you,&nbsp;&nbsp;which you may obtain as follows:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If you are a &#8220;stockholder of record&#8221; with shares registered directly in your name with our&nbsp;&nbsp;transfer agent, Computershare Trust Company (a minority of </font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla stockholders), you can&nbsp;&nbsp;find the control number on the Notice of Internet Availability or paper proxy card that was&nbsp;&nbsp;sent to you (please check that it is for the meeting as scheduled for September 22, 2020,&nbsp;&nbsp;NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 20</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">20).&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are a &#8220;beneficial owner&#8221; and hold shares through a broker, bank or other&nbsp;&nbsp;organization (the vast majority of Tesla stockholders), you will have to register in advance&nbsp;&nbsp;to obtain a control number. Please ask your broker, bank or organization fo</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">r a &#8220;legal&nbsp;&nbsp;proxy&#8221; for the 2020 Annual Meeting and submit a copy of it from your e-mail address with&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;Legal Proxy&#8221; in the subject line to legalproxy@computershare.com. If your request is&nbsp;&nbsp;received no later than 2:00 PM Pacific Time on September 17, 2020, </font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">you will receive a&nbsp;&nbsp;confirmation e-mail with your control number.&nbsp;&nbsp;Limited&nbsp;&nbsp;In-Person&nbsp;&nbsp;Events&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, we expect to accommodate a very limited number of stockholders in-person at&nbsp;&nbsp;the 2020 Annual Meeting and the Battery Day event due to mandated res</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">trictions on the size&nbsp;&nbsp;of in-person gatherings. through&nbsp;&nbsp;receipt&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;valid&nbsp;&nbsp;government-issued&nbsp;&nbsp;identification.&nbsp;&nbsp;Selections&nbsp;&nbsp;are non-transferable.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please&nbsp;&nbsp;carefully review&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;2020&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual&nbsp;&nbsp;Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Battery&nbsp;&nbsp;Day must&nbsp;&nbsp;match&nbsp;&nbsp;your&nbsp;&nbsp;government-issued&nbsp;&nbsp;identification&nbsp;&nbsp;exactly.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please&nbsp;&nbsp;review&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;types&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;valid&nbsp;&nbsp;evidence of&nbsp;&nbsp;stock&nbsp;&nbsp;ownership&nbsp;&nbsp;as&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;July <p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU10"></a>Country&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;United States&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proof of Ownership on July 31, 2020&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No File Selected&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CHOOSE A FILE I have read and agree to the 2020 Annual Meeting &amp; Battery Day Drawing Terms.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SUBMIT I understand that if selected, I will be required to submit additional documentation of eligibility&nbsp;&nbsp;to attend this&nbsp;&nbsp;event.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;"><br /></font></p>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gutg0ctw442q000006.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:623px;height:807px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;"></font></p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU11"></a><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2020&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual&nbsp;&nbsp;Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Battery&nbsp;&nbsp;Day&nbsp;&nbsp;Drawing&nbsp;&nbsp;Terms&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Participation. Tesla will conduct a random drawing to determine its stockhol</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ders&#8217; eligibility&nbsp;&nbsp;to attend its 2020 Annual Meeting and separate Battery Day event in person. The drawing will&nbsp;&nbsp;be held strictly in accordance with these 2020 Annual Meeting &amp; Battery Day Drawing Terms&nbsp;&nbsp;(&#8220;Terms&#8221;), and no exceptions will be made. Participa</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">tion is voluntary and does not create a&nbsp;&nbsp;legal partnership, agency, or other relationship between an applicant and Tesla. Entries must&nbsp;&nbsp;be made by Friday, August 28, 2020 at 11:59 PM Pacific Time. Incomplete applications or&nbsp;&nbsp;attempted applications by means</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> other than through the online application form will not be&nbsp;&nbsp;considered.&nbsp;&nbsp;NO PURCHASE OR PAYMENT OF ANY KIND IS NECESSARY TO APPLY OR BE SELECTED. A&nbsp;&nbsp;PURCHASE OR PAYMENT WILL NOT INCREASE AN APPLICANT&#8217;S CHANCES OF BEING&nbsp;&nbsp;SELECTED. DRAWING IS VOID WHERE PRO</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">HIBITED BY APPLICABLE LAW.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;By participating in the drawing, each applicant certifies that such applicant is of the legal age&nbsp;&nbsp;of majority in the jurisdiction in which such applicant resides (at least 18 years of age in many&nbsp;&nbsp;countries) and such applican</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">t represents that such applicant is a stockholder and is legally&nbsp;&nbsp;permitted to participate.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligibility. Each applicant will be required to submit proper evidence of stock ownership as&nbsp;&nbsp;of July 31, 2020, which must be one of the following and must s</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">how the name of the&nbsp;&nbsp;stockholder:&nbsp;&nbsp;For &#8220;stockholders of record&#8221; on July 31, 2020,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a &#8220;Notice of Internet Availability&#8221; or paper proxy card that was sent to the stockholder&nbsp;&nbsp;(please check that it is for the meeting as scheduled for September 22, 2020, NO</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">T as&nbsp;&nbsp;previously scheduled for July 7, 2020); or&nbsp;&nbsp;a statement of ownership from Tesla&#8217;s transfer agent, Computershare, confirming stock&nbsp;&nbsp;ownership as of July 31, 2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;For &#8220;beneficial owners&#8221; on July 31, 2020,</font><font style="font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><img src="gutg0ctw442q000007.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:623px;height:807px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;"></font></p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU12"></a><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">a notice regarding the 2020 Annual Meeti</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ng received from the broker, bank or other&nbsp;&nbsp;organization through which shares were held (please check that it is for the meeting as&nbsp;&nbsp;scheduled for September 22, 2020, NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 2020); or&nbsp;&nbsp;a &#8220;legal proxy&#8221; document from such org</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">anization indicating the stockholder&#8217;s authority to&nbsp;&nbsp;vote the shares at the 2020 Annual Meeting (please check that it is for the meeting as&nbsp;&nbsp;scheduled for September 22, 2020, NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 2020); or&nbsp;&nbsp;a statement or letter from suc</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">h organization confirming stock ownership as of July 31,&nbsp;&nbsp;2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;If selected, an applicant will be asked to submit a copy of valid government-issued&nbsp;&nbsp;identification and, where applicable, proof of address for such applicant. If the applicant is the&nbsp;&nbsp;stockh</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">older and is a natural person, the name shown on such identification must match the&nbsp;&nbsp;name shown on the submitted evidence of stock ownership, as well as the name on the&nbsp;&nbsp;application. If the applicant represents a stockholder that is an entity, such applica</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">nt will also&nbsp;&nbsp;be asked to submit acceptable evidence of such applicant&#8217;s legal ability to represent the&nbsp;&nbsp;stockholder, which must match the name shown on such identification. Acceptable&nbsp;&nbsp;government-issuedidentification must, at a minimum, include the applic</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ant&#8217;s current photo, full&nbsp;&nbsp;name, address or place of birth, identification number, and date of birth. If a selected applicant&nbsp;&nbsp;cannot satisfy these requirements in a timely manner, the selection will be forfeited.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;THERE IS A MAXIMUM OF ONE APPLICATION P</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ER STOCKHOLDER. TESLA WILL SCREEN&nbsp;&nbsp;FOR MULTIPLE APPLICATIONS BY OR ON BEHALF OF THE SAME STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;&nbsp;(INCLUDING REPRESENTATIVES OF THE SAME STOCKHOLDER ENTITY), AND ALL&nbsp;&nbsp;IDENTIFIED MULTIPLE APPLICATIONS BY OR ON BEHALF OF A STOCKHOLDER WILL BE&nbsp;&nbsp;DISQUALIFI</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ED.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Guests. Each application is personal to the applicant submitting it. If an applicant is&nbsp;&nbsp;selected, under no circumstances will a spouse, domestic partner, child, or other family&nbsp;&nbsp;member or guest of such applicant (including a joint owner of shar</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">es) be admitted to the&nbsp;&nbsp;events unless such other person has separately applied for the drawing in his or her capacity&nbsp;&nbsp;as a stockholder and been selected. If the stockholder is an entity, only its legal representative&nbsp;&nbsp;who applies for and is selected in th</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">e drawing will be eligible for admission.&nbsp;&nbsp;4.&nbsp;&nbsp;General Conditions. All determinations by Tesla with respect to the drawing or any&nbsp;&nbsp;applicant&#8217;s eligibility will be final. Tesla, in its sole discretion, will determine the validity of each&nbsp;&nbsp;application. If Te</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">sla determines or believes that any application is fraudulent, illegitimate or&nbsp;&nbsp;invalid, or that any applicant has failed to comply with or has violated any provision of these&nbsp;&nbsp;Terms, Tesla will have the right in its discretion to disqualify any affected a</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">pplicant(s).&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla reserves the right to modify these procedures or whether and how the in-person portion&nbsp;&nbsp;of the events will be held in its sole discretion. Tesla may be required to or choose to further&nbsp;&nbsp;change the date, time, location and/or format of t</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">he events. Irrespective of changes in&nbsp;&nbsp;schedule, government travel restrictions or other foreseeable and unforeseeable events,&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla will not be responsible for any travel or lodging arrangements made or other expenses&nbsp;&nbsp;incurred in anticipation or further</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ance of attending the events in person.</font><font style="font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><img src="gutg0ctw442q000008.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:623px;height:807px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;"></font></p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU13"></a><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">INVITATIONS TO ATTEND THE EVENTS ARE NOT TRANSFERABLE AND ANY ATTEMPT TO&nbsp;&nbsp;TRANSFER AN INVITATION TO ANY OTHER PERSON WILL BE VOID AND WILL RESULT IN&nbsp;&nbsp;SUCH INVITATION BEING RESCINDED.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5.&nbsp;&nbsp;Release and Limitatio</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ns. By participating in this drawing, and to the extent there are any&nbsp;&nbsp;media recordings (photograph/video) of the event, each applicant authorizes and releases&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla, or its respective licensees, affiliates, successors, and assignees the right, where&nbsp;&nbsp;per</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">mitted by law, without any further notice, review or consent to print, publish, broadcast,&nbsp;&nbsp;distribute, and use, worldwide in any media now known or hereafter in perpetuity and on a&nbsp;&nbsp;worldwide basis, the photographs, images or video shared or captured with</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> or on behalf of&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla, including, without limitation, the content of media including subjects captured,&nbsp;&nbsp;associated content, voice, likeness, image or statements, as well as metadata information for&nbsp;&nbsp;any purpose including but not limited to news, publici</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ty, advertising, public relations, or other&nbsp;&nbsp;promotional purposes without any expectation of compensation or remuneration now or in the&nbsp;&nbsp;future.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each applicant also agrees that Tesla will have no liability for, and shall be held harmless by&nbsp;&nbsp;such applican</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">t against, any liability for any injuries, losses or damages of any kind to persons,&nbsp;&nbsp;including personal injury or death, or property resulting in whole or in part, directly or&nbsp;&nbsp;indirectly, from acceptance, or participation in this drawing, or any claims b</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ased on publicity&nbsp;&nbsp;rights, defamation or invasion of privacy. The released parties are not responsible if any&nbsp;&nbsp;eligibility is revoked due to cancellations, delays, or interruptions due to acts of God, acts of&nbsp;&nbsp;war, natural disasters, weather, or terrorism.</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notification of Selection. Each selected applicant will be notified by direct email using the&nbsp;&nbsp;email address provided during the application. Each selected applicant must respond to the&nbsp;&nbsp;direct email message within forty-eight (48) hours after the </font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">direct email message is sent. If&nbsp;&nbsp;such selected applicant does not respond to the direct email message with a submission of&nbsp;&nbsp;legible and complete copy of any additional proper evidence demonstrating eligibility to&nbsp;&nbsp;attend this event as described in Section</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> 2, such selected applicant may be disqualified, and&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla reserves the right to select an alternative applicant at random.&nbsp;&nbsp;7.&nbsp;&nbsp;Conduct. By participating in this drawing, each applicant agrees in advance, if selected, to&nbsp;&nbsp;conduct himself or herself at th</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">e events in a responsible, professional and courteous manner,&nbsp;&nbsp;free from disruptive behavior, including foul language and obscene gestures (as well as any&nbsp;&nbsp;obscene or indecent messages on signs or clothing). Each selected applicant will further&nbsp;&nbsp;comply wit</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">h local California public health authority requirements, requests from Tesla staff&nbsp;&nbsp;regarding safety and any changes to operations and/or emergency response procedures. Any&nbsp;&nbsp;lack of adherence to this code of conduct may result in permanent disqualification</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> from future&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla events, as well as potential violation of local ordinances resulting in possible arrest and&nbsp;&nbsp;prosecution.&nbsp;&nbsp;8.&nbsp;&nbsp;Governing Law. Any litigation or dispute resolution between the applicant and Tesla arising&nbsp;&nbsp;out of or relating to these Term</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">s, will take place in the Northern District of California, and each&nbsp;&nbsp;applicant and Tesla hereby consent to the personal jurisdiction of and exclusive venue in the&nbsp;&nbsp;state and federal courts within that District with respect to any such litigation or dispute</font><font style="color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;resolution. This Agreement will be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of</font><font style="font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><img src="gutg0ctw442q000009.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:623px;height:807px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;"></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> the United States and the State of California, except that body of California law concerning&nbsp;&nbsp;conflicts of law.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;9.&nbsp;&nbsp;Privacy. Each applicant applying for a chance to attend the events in-person acknowledges&nbsp;&nbsp;and understands that the application information submitted may be stored and processed in&nbsp;&nbsp;any country which Tesla has facilities or in which Tesla engages service providers. Those&nbsp;&nbsp;countries may not have the same data protection laws as the country in which an applicant&nbsp;&nbsp;initially provided that information. When Tesla transfers information from or about an applicant&nbsp;&nbsp;to other countries, Tesla will protect it as described in Tesla's Privacy Notice. By submitting&nbsp;&nbsp;your application, or otherwise providing information to Tesla, each applicant consents to the&nbsp;&nbsp;transfer of information from or about such applicant to countries outside of such applicant&#8217;s&nbsp;&nbsp;country of residence, including the United States. Applicant information will not be used for&nbsp;&nbsp;marketing, and processed and retained only for the purposes described herein, and in&nbsp;&nbsp;accordance with Tesla's Privacy Notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
